RACE.FOOTNOTES: STOLEN FUTURE three then two wide in closest aim of the leader, came under coaxing near the quarter pole before being set down spinning three wide for home, rallied to take command straightened away, dug in under a drive under lone threat and held gamely to prevail. LOON CRY chased three then two wide coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, swung four wide into upper stretch, rallied to issue a challenge through the final furlong but was ultimately repelled at the end while along clear of the rest and second best. CERRETTA coaxed from the gate, chased just off the inside until set down angled out six wide into upper stretch, offered up a mild kick to secure the show honors. MZ BIG BUCKS coaxed from the gate, chased along the inside coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, swung three wide into upper stretch, kept on to the finish to secure the last major share, then lost rider when returning from the gallop out, briefly ran off before being apprehended by outrider. MY CARA MIA MINE three wide in pursuit, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, angled five to six wide into upper stretch and offered no response. CENTRAL SPEED four wide in pursuit from mid pack, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, bid five wide into upper stretch, got put to a right handed crop and ducked in directly in front of AUTUMN at the three-sixteenths, had that foe clip the back of her heels and fall heavily forcing LADY LAOBAN to then fall over her, then weakened to the finish. BUSHWICK chased three then two wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, angled three to four wide into upper stretch and made no impact. PHINNEYS HARBOR coaxed from the gate, showed the way in hand through swift splits just off the inside, tucked inside through the turn coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch, yielded the front straightened away and folded. LADY LAOBAN bobbled at the start, recovered to tracked the pace along the inside from mid pack, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch, had AUTUMN fall heavily directly in front when clipping the heels of CENTRAL SPEED when that rival ducked in at the three-sixteenths and had no chance to avoid the fallen foe falling directly over her and into the railing, recovered to her feet sans rider and ran off briefly before being apprehended by the outrider and was subsequently vanned off. AUTUMN just off the inside in pursuit from mid pack, tucked inside through the turn coming under light coaxing at the three-eighths, swung four wide into upper stretch, had CENTRAL SPEED duck in sharply under a right handed crop with three-sixteenths to go and clipped heels with the back of that rival falling heavily into the fence before LADY LAOBAN fell over her, got up under her own power and ran off clockwise and was apprehended by the outrider and subsequently walked off under her own power. There was a Stewards' Inquiry into the stretch run focusing on the incident at the three-sixteenths. After review, CENTRAL SPEED was disqualified from sixth place and placed last before the result was declared official.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JOEY FRESHWATER coaxed from the gate, chased four then three wide under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, took over command swinging four wide into upper stretch, edged away under a drive to prevail. GILMORE traded a bump at the start with VICTORY WAY, chased three then two wide coming under coaxing at the seven-sixteenths, angled three to four wide into upper stretch and closed well in the late stages to just get up in the very last jump for the place honors. VICTORY WAY traded a bump at the start with GILMORE, pressed the pace of PROVE RIGHT from the inside while just off the rail, tucked to the fence into the turn and came under coaxing at the three-eighths, advanced to take over narrow and brief command at the five-sixteenths, got headed spinning just off the inside for home, dug in under a drive running on and was nailed on the wire for the place honors. EXPECTED VALUE broke out at the start bumping PROVE RIGHT in the hindquarters, chased three wide under a ride from three furlongs out, angled seven wide at the head of the stretch and offered up late foot to close in concert with GILMORE to his inside but got out-finished in the late going. DAYDREAMING BOY five then four wide in pursuit, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, went six wide into upper stretch, offered up a mild bid but was outkicked. PROVE RIGHT got bumped in the hind end at the start by EXPECTED VALUE, who broke outwards, established the front shortly after and showed the way in hand three then two wide under pressure to the inside from VICTORY WAY, came under coaxing at the three-eighths now under threat from flanking rivals, yielded the front with five-sixteenths to go and angled five wide into upper stretch in the midst of being shaken off, then weakened through to the finish. ARREBATO coaxed from the gate, chased along the inside under coaxing from the seven-sixteenths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOPPELGANGER away well, quickly dropped back and chased five to six paths off the inside down the backstretch, tucked to the two path through the turn coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, angled four to five wide into upper stretch, closed well to issue a challenge nearing the final sixteenth, overthrew a trio seventy yards from home to take over, then prevailed edging away to the finish to score. TODAY'S FLAVOR coaxed from the start, cut the pace just off the inside under pressure from a pair, lost one of those rivals when LITTLE VIC decided he wanted to be the lone pace pressure and pinched EXPRESSMAN out just inside the half mile pole, knocked heads with LITTLE VIC through the turn and was set down taking the inside route into upper stretch, dug in under a drive shaking off that rival confronted by a pair, dug in and was overwhelmed with seventy yards to the finish and was out-finished in the late stages. BOLD JOURNEY chased along the inside from the tail of the field, came under coaxing just off the inside at the seven-sixteenths, angled out five to six wide into upper stretch and made no late headway. LITTLE VIC prompted the pace outside a pair four paths off the inside, tucked three wide bumping EXPRESSMAN to the two path in behind the leader forcing that rival to steady off heels, advanced to duel for command three wide through the turn coming under coaxing near the five-sixteenths, spun two to three wide into upper stretch on near even terms, got shaken off a furlong out and weakened through to the finish, then was reported to have bled.

(UP TO $14,268 NYSBFOA) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $18,000 OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER OR STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 127 lbs. Non-winners O f A Race Other Than Claiming Or Starter At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. (If No Three Year Olds Are Entered, Starting Weight Shall Be 122 lbs). (If the Stewards consider it inadvisable to run this race on the turf course, this race will be run at One Mile on the Main Track.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VERONICA GREENE was bumped at the start then forced out, came under restraint early, went around the first turn in the three path, settled towards the back while unhurried, was roused while moving from the two path to the four path around the final turn, rallied five wide into the stretch, closed strongly to get the lead coming to the furlong marker, fought outside of the runner-up to the sixteenth-pole and proved best under good handling. EXPAND THE MAP (IRE) was taken in hand early then taken back, saved ground on the first turn, was reserved of the pace, came under urging while two then three wide around the far turn, rallied four wide into the stretch, closed well to make a bid nearing the furlong marker, battled with the winner to near the sixteenth-pole then was outfinished while clear for the place. CANDLE traveled around the first turn in the three path, settled well behind the runaway leader in second position, was urged along in the two path on the far turn, gained three wide into the stretch, made a bid outside the furlong marker but was out-kicked while able to get the show. CAIRONI settled on the inside, was roused on the far turn, moved out in upper stretch, came further out near the furlong marker and lacked the needed response. YO CUZ was sent to the front, opened up a sizable advantage while inside to the two path, shortened stride in the two path around the far turn, was swallowed up while under the crop outside the furlong marker and tired. INTO HAPPINESS settled at the rear, saved ground on both turns and was no factor. GEYSER ROAD broke out and bumped with a foe, rounded the first turn in the two path, settled off the pace, dropped back three then four wide around the far turn and had nothing left.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 10 6F Outer turf CR: 77. Maiden Special Weight Purse 70000. OUTER TURF FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred)(If No Three Year Olds Are Entered, Starting Weight Shall Be 122 lbs).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WEEKEND RAGS vied from the four path early on before backing away a bit briefly, advanced once more and tucked three wide through the turn to prompt the pace from the outside, came under coaxing near the quarter pole, spun just off the inside into upper stretch, took over command at the three-sixteenths and edged clear under a drive to prevail. SNOWY EVENING chased just off the inside until tucked inside through the turn, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, spun three wide for home and offered up a late surge to get up for the place honors. STRICTLY TABOO bumped at the start by LAKESIDE GETAWAY, vied from the two path with a pair before emerging to slug it out with WEEKEND RAGS through the turn while tucked inside, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, took the inside route into upper stretch and was headed for the front with three-sixteenths to go, then kept on under a drive to the finish. SHE'S A NATURAL bumped at the start by CHARISSE, who broke inwards, chased just off the inside until tucked inside through the turn coming under coaxing at he three-eighths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch and improved position to the wire. RED HOT CHICK three to four paths off the inside down the backstretch, tucked to the two path through the turn coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, angled five wide into upper stretch and offered no response. ADMIRE MY CROWN vied inside a pair early on, then got shaken off a bit and chased through the turn under coaxing from midway, angled three wide into upper stretch and weakened in the late stages. CHARISSE broke in at the start bumping SHE'S A NATURAL, chased just off the inside until tucked inside through the turn, came under coaxing three furlongs from home, angled four to five wide into upper stretch and passed tired rivals. LAKESIDE GETAWAY broke out at the start bumping STRICTLY TABOO, chased just off the inside under a ride from the three-eighths, angled four wide for home and weakened in the late going. LIMANI three wide in pursuit, came under coaxing three furlongs from home, angled five to six wide into upper stretch, weakened in the drive. GALATRONA chased three to four wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, angled eight wide into upper stretch, tired, then lost the rider when returning from the gallop out and ran away loose until apprehended by outrider. PRACTICAL JULIA five then four wide in pursuit down the backstretch, went four wide through the turn losing ground, got eased up near the quarter pole and was cantering to the finish when suffering an injury to the left hind leg near the sixteenth pole, was immediately pulled up inside that station and was subsequently vanned off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Wood Memorial S. Presented by Resorts World Casino - Grade2 AQUEDUCT RACE 11 1 1/8M Dirt CR: 97. Stakes Purse 750000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LORD MILES bumped with a rival at the start, established a forward position early, went three wide around the first turn, raced up close on the outside, was asked in the four path on the far turn, gained under a drive into upper stretch, made a bid outside of three foes inside the three-sixteenths, came in slightly under a right-handed crop and jostled with the runner-up outside the sixteenth-pole, jostled again with that foe inside that pole, rubbed saddles while battling with two opponents to the wire and gamely prevailed at big odds. HIT SHOW moved in some early, went four wide around the opening bend, settled just off the pace, was given his cue in the three path while inside of the winner on the far turn, moved out for room under a left-handed crop in upper stretch, made a bid between foes inside the three-sixteenths, jostled with the winner outside the sixteenth-pole then again inside that pole, continued to fight between foes while rubbing saddles to the wire and was denied while just able to get the place. DREAMLIKE was hustled from the gate then taken in hand nearing the first turn, traveled around that bend in the two path, was well placed just off the pace, moved out late on the backstretch, issued a challenge under urging in the four then three path on the final turn, turned into upper stretch under a drive, fought on gamely inside of two opponents in the final furlong, rubbed saddles some with the runner-up starting outside the sixteenth-pole and just missed while well clear for the show. ARCTIC ARROGANCE was hustled from the gate, angled in while going to the front, saved ground on the first turn, set a joint pace on the inside of a foe, vied in the two path under pressure on the far turn, battled under a drive into the final furlong and weakened. CLASSIC CATCH dropped back between foes early, rounded the first turn in the four path, was urged along towards the rear on the backstretch, moved from four to six wide around the far turn and failed to threaten. SLIP MAHONEY bumped hard with a foe while bumping with another rival into the first turn then checked sharply, settled off the pace, moved from the inside to the four path under urging on the far turn and came up empty. SHADOW DRAGON traveled around the first turn in the two path, settled towards the back, angled from the three path to the five path while roused on the far turn and was no factor. KNOX was bumped in the hindquarters into the first turn, raced in the three path around that bend, settled off the pace, was urged along in the two path on the far turn and lacked the needed response. CRUPI bumped with a rival at the start then was snatched up with the right-rein, moved in early, dropped from the three path to the rail on the first turn, was urged along on the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn and never reached contention. GENERAL BANKER bumped hard with a rival while also making contact with another opponent into the first turn then checked sharply, settled off the pace, was urged two then three wide around the far turn and came up empty. MR. SWAGGER bumped with a rival into the first turn then was taken up in tight quarters, went four wide on the first turn, was reserved off the pace, traveled four wide under urging on the final turn and failed to respond. UNCLE JAKE was in tight just after the start, became rank behind foes while under tight restraint early then moved out, went five wide around the first turn, pulled his way forward late on that bend, set a joint pace on the outside, came up empty while dropping from the three path to the rail on the far turn and retreated. FOLLOWING A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INTO THE STRETCH RUN, NO CHANGE WAS MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH
